pageTitle: Itinerary for Wednesday, January 25, 2017 | Prime Minister of Canada
articleHtml:
Itinerary for the Prime Minister, Justin Trudeau, for Wednesday, January 25, 2017:

Calgary, Alberta

9:00 a.m. The Prime Minister will attend a meeting of the Prime Minister’s Youth Council.

Notes for media:

  • Pooled photo opportunity

Saskatoon, Saskatchewan

4:40 p.m. The Prime Minister will meet with the Saskatoon City Council.

Note for media:

  • Pooled photo opportunity


5:45 p.m. The Prime Minister will hold a media availability.

Health Sciences Building, Room 2334
University of Saskatchewan
107 Wiggins Road
Saskatoon, Saskatchewan

Notes for media:

  • Open coverage
  • Media should arrive no later than 5:15 p.m.


7:00 p.m. The Prime Minister will participate in a town hall Q&A.

The Dubé Theatre
Health Sciences Building, Room 1150
University of Saskatchewan
107 Wiggins Road
Saskatoon, Saskatchewan

Notes for media:

  • Open coverage
  • Media should arrive no later than 5:15 p.m.


Note: All times local
